SIMPLE: timbered
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Timbered
<hw>Tim"bered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Furnished with timber; -- often compounded; <as>as, a
well-<ex>timbered</ex> house; a low-<ex>timbered</ex> house</as>.</def>
<rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Built; formed; contrived.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Massive, like timber.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>timbered</qex> bones all broken, rudely rumbled.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Covered with growth timber; wooden; <as>as,
well-<ex>timbered</ex> land</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Timberhead</ent>⟦br⟧
